page.title: 09WOODLAND SOUTH OF BARRHEAD
page.content:
The{WOODLAND}adjacent to{GLANDERSTON {DAM}is typical of the area and consists of two main parts.
The{Coniferous}part contains larch and pine trees and virtually nothing grows on the ground underneath this section.
The{Deciduous}part contains mainly sycamore and rowan trees and much more grows on the ground in this section. Here and in the clearings can be found grasses, bluebells, bracken, gorse, brambles, moss, foxglove and bedstraw.
Many{birds}can be heard including song thrush, blackbird, robin, chaffinch, great tit and willow warbler.
The woodland also provides{cover}for deer, fox, rabbit and squirrel.
